FileCore_DescribeDisc  (&40545)
#Parent FileCore_
=>	R0 =	pointer to disc name (or :0, etc)
	R1 =	<pointer to data block=>FileCore_disc>
	R8 =	pointer to FileCore instance private word

This call allows you to check the disc's format and internal structure. If the disc specified is not in a drive it will be searched for and asked for in an error box or by prompt. If the disc name is that of a drive then if no disc is present then the Drive empty error will be reported.
#Line
See <PRM 2, page 232=>PRM-2:232>.
